"title": "2333: Jesus Christ, attitude to OT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2333",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ's teaching was based largely on the OT, which he treated as God's inspired and authoritative word, but which he had the authority to interpret.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ recognises the OT as Scripture</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ calls the OT ``Scripture''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:35\">JHN 10:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:10\">MRK 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:24\">MRK 12:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:29\">MAT 22:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:21\">LUK 4:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:39\">JHN 5:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:38\">JHN 7:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:18\">JHN 13:18</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ underlines the authority of the OT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:46-John5:47\">JHN 5:46–5:47</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The OT is authoritative over Jesus Christ's opponents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:23\">MAT 23:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:19-Matt5:20\">MAT 5:19–5:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:2-Matt23:3\">MAT 23:2–23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:24-Mark2:27\">MRK 2:24–2:27</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:2-Matt12:6\">MAT 12:2–12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:2-Luke6:4\">LUK 6:2–6:4</a></p>\n<h3>The OT is authoritative over Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:4\">LUK 4:4</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:3\">DEU 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:7\">MAT 4:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:12\">LUK 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:16\">DEU 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10\">MAT 4:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:8\">LUK 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13\">DEU 6:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ regards the OT as being fulfilled in himself</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ regards his ministry as fulfilling the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17-Matt5:18\">MAT 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:4-Matt11:6\">MAT 11:4–11:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:22-Luke7:23\">LUK 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:56\">MAT 26:56</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:49\">MRK 14:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:17-Luke4:21\">LUK 4:17–4:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:25\">JHN 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:19\">PSA 35:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:4\">PSA 69:4</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ regards his death as fulfilling OT prophecy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:32\">LUK 18:31–18:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:39-Matt12:40\">MAT 12:39–12:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:28\">MAT 26:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20\">LUK 22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:31\">MAT 26:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:27\">MRK 14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:7\">ZEC 13:7</a></p>\n<h3>Other aspects of the OT fulfilled or affirmed by Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:12\">MAT 7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:10\">MAT 11:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:27\">LUK 7:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:1\">MAL 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:14-Matt13:15\">MAT 13:14–13:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:12\">MRK 4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:10\">LUK 8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:9-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:9–6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:11-Matt17:12\">MAT 17:11–17:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:12-Mark9:13\">MRK 9:12–9:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:5\">MAL 4:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:15\">MAT 24:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:14\">MRK 13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:20\">LUK 21:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:27\">DAN 9:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:31\">DAN 11:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:11\">DAN 12:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ confirms the OT teaching about judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:41-Matt12:42\">MAT 12:41–12:42</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:30-Luke11:32\">LUK 11:30–11:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:23\">MAT 11:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:12-Luke10:15\">LUK 10:12–10:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ interprets OT teaching</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ interprets OT teaching about the Sabbath</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:25-Mark2:28\">MRK 2:25–2:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:3-Matt12:8\">MAT 12:3–12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:3-Luke6:5\">LUK 6:3–6:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ interprets OT teaching about religious practices</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:13\">MAT 9:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:6\">HOS 6:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:7-Matt15:8\">MAT 15:7–15:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:6-Mark7:7\">MRK 7:6–7:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:13\">ISA 29:13</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ interprets OT teaching about purity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:18-Mark7:19\">MRK 7:18–7:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:17\">MAT 15:17</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ interprets OT teaching about family life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:31-Matt5:32\">MAT 5:31–5:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:4-Matt15:6\">MAT 15:4–15:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:10-Mark7:13\">MRK 7:10–7:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:17\">EXO 21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:9\">LEV 20:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:1-Matt19:9\">MAT 19:1–19:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:2-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:2–10:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ interprets OT teaching about retaliation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:38-Matt5:42\">MAT 5:38–5:42</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ refers to the OT in his teaching</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:18\">MAT 19:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:19\">MRK 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:20\">LUK 18:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12-Exod20:16\">EXO 20:12–20:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16-Deut5:20\">DEU 5:16–5:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:31-Matt22:32\">MAT 22:31–22:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:26-Mark12:27\">MRK 12:26–12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:37-Luke20:38\">LUK 20:37–20:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:37-Matt24:39\">MAT 24:37–24:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:26-Luke17:27\">LUK 17:26–17:27</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ uses the language of the OT</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:29\">MRK 4:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:13\">JOL 3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:18\">MRK 8:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:10\">ISA 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:48\">MRK 9:48</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:24\">ISA 66:24</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ appeals to the OT in its entirety</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:50-Luke11:51\">LUK 11:50–11:51</a></strong> <em>The murders of Abel and Zechariah occur in the first (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:8\">Ge 4:8</a>) and last (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:21\">2Ch 24:21</a>) books of the Hebrew OT (Chronicles comes at the close of the OT according to the Hebrew arrangement).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:27\">LUK 24:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:44\">LUK 24:44</a> <em>The Law, the Prophets and the Psalms are the three divisions of the Hebrew OT.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ treats the OT as a true historical record</h2>\n<p>The patriarchs:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11\">MAT 8:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:56\">JHN 8:56</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:58\">JHN 8:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:4\">MAT 8:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:44\">MRK 1:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:14\">LUK 5:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:8\">MAT 19:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:5\">MRK 10:5</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:29\">MAT 6:29</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:27\">LUK 12:27</a> <em>Solomon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:12\">MAT 5:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:23\">LUK 6:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:25-Luke4:27\">LUK 4:25–4:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:45\">JHN 6:45</a></p>",
